## Analyses Identified in the Paper

Based on [noms_v4.tex](file:///home/breno/doutorado/ec2sweetspot_noms/ec2sweetspot_noms/IEEE-conference-template-062824/noms_v4.tex), Phase 2 performs:

| # | Analysis | Description | Script |
|---|----------|-------------|--------|
| 1 | **Log Parsing** | Extract compression times from [.log](file:///home/breno/doutorado/ec2sweetspot_noms/ec2sweetspot_noms/artifacts/t3_micro_phase1.log) files into per-instance CSVs | [parser.py](file:///home/breno/doutorado/ec2sweetspot_noms/ec2sweetspot_noms/artifacts/scripts/processing/parser.py) |
| 2 | **Descriptive Statistics** | Median, Std, Min, Max for Compression Time per (Instance, Codec, Threads) | [generate_descriptive_stats_table.py](file:///home/breno/doutorado/ec2sweetspot_noms/ec2sweetspot_noms/artifacts/scripts/processing/generate_descriptive_stats_table.py) |
| 3 | **Efficiency Calculation** | `Efficiency = 1 / (cost/3600 × time)` — normalized performance-cost metric | [generate_descriptive_stats_table.py](file:///home/breno/doutorado/ec2sweetspot_noms/ec2sweetspot_noms/artifacts/scripts/processing/generate_descriptive_stats_table.py) |
| 4 | **Total Cost** | `Total Cost = (hourly_cost/3600) × time` — monetary cost per operation | Manual calc |
| 5 | **Statistical Tests** | Shapiro-Wilk (normality), Levene's (variance), Welch's t-test (significance) | New script needed |
| 6 | **Bar Charts** | Median compression time per codec (3 charts: H.264, H.265, VP9) | [generate_performance_plots.py](file:///home/breno/doutorado/ec2sweetspot_noms/ec2sweetspot_noms/artifacts/scripts/processing/generate_performance_plots.py) |
| 7 | **Heatmaps** | Efficiency heatmap per codec (threads × instance type) | [generate_performance_plots.py](file:///home/breno/doutorado/ec2sweetspot_noms/ec2sweetspot_noms/artifacts/scripts/processing/generate_performance_plots.py) |
| 8 | **Sunburst Diagram** | Hierarchical efficiency visualization across all configs | [generate_performance_plots.py](file:///home/breno/doutorado/ec2sweetspot_noms/ec2sweetspot_noms/artifacts/scripts/processing/generate_performance_plots.py) |
| 9 | **Key Insights** | Cost-efficiency comparison, thread scaling patterns, codec-specific behavior | Written analysis |

